  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nAt the moment our UI is homogenised to a follow a single design, skewed towards iOS, without taking platform specific patterns into account. While in past this allowed us to design more rapidly and keep the codebase simpler, this doesn't always take into account what's good for our users. \r\nBy implementing these Android specific assets, we will make the experience more familiar to our users and in line with best platform practices and expectations.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### 1. Implement platform specific `Share` icon\r\n\r\n<img width=\"760\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-02-24 at 10 02 38\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/75140228-c2e1bb00-56ee-11ea-895a-e77763ea08a9.png\">\r\n\r\n### 2. For the back button, on iOS we should use the `<` chevron or `x` when it's a modal dialogue (like we do now). On Android `<` should be replaced with a `‚Üê`.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1140\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-02-24 at 10 18 16\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/75140340-fc1a2b00-56ee-11ea-8cc0-0a570583a8b9.png\">\r\n\r\n### 3. Do not use disclosure indicators on Android. ( `>` chevrons in list items )\r\nThis is an iOS only pattern, simple as that :)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1150\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-02-24 at 10 22 18\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/75141045-6ed7d600-56f0-11ea-80be-639156849b7f.png\">\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nAll items on the list were implemented and tested, if necessary, appropriate steps were taken so that it's handled on component level. \r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThanks! üôè \r\n",
